						<summary>

						<p>Stone standing in the compound of Mahāliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 12th-13th century.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record seems to refer to an agreement the enjoyment of income from certain taxes, entered into by <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> <hi rend="bold">Oḍamadēvarasa,</hi> <hi rend="italic">atikāri</hi> Nāraṇ-āḷuya, the Threehundred of H2ākaḷa, Twelve <hi rend="italic">mahajanas</hi> of Harika and others. The record is undated.</p>						

						</summary>
